      "id": "a8665c6a_b43df7c3",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/main/rest/StatisticsRestControllerV1.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 116,
      "message": "I had originally had it as fromDate & toDate, to match audit.  However, then I noticed that the statistics records, themselves, use the name timeStamp instead of \"date\".  In addition, policy/models uses startTime & endTime all over the place.  Consequently, I reversed direction and went with startTime & endTime, instead.\n\nI did just check the audit records, and they use \"timestamp\", so if you want to change to startTime/endTime, that would be fine, too.\n\n(Hmm, I need to update the pap api docs to reflect the addition of these new parameters...)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
